&gt;&gt; Brian Holt: So parents and children.

2
00:00:02.740 --> 00:00:07.464
So something first I want to tell you
is you would typically call &lt;div&gt; here,

3
00:00:07.464 --> 00:00:08.906
the parent of &lt;h1&gt;.

4
00:00:08.906 --> 00:00:11.030
It's because it encapsulates.

5
00:00:11.030 --> 00:00:15.310
So that relationship is called &lt;div&gt;
is the parent, &lt;h1&gt; is the child.

6
00:00:16.410 --> 00:00:21.732
And if I had one above &lt;div&gt;, like maybe
there was a section above &lt;div&gt; here,

7
00:00:21.732 --> 00:00:24.678
you would call that it's ancestor, right?

8
00:00:24.678 --> 00:00:29.264
Cuz it's even further that a parent.
&gt;&gt; Brian Holt: And then,

9
00:00:29.264 --> 00:00:34.300
if h1 had another paragraph next to it,
it would be its sibling.

10
00:00:34.300 --> 00:00:35.518
I'm not making this up,

11
00:00:35.518 --> 00:00:39.964
that's what people call it.
&gt;&gt; Brian Holt: So

12
00:00:39.964 --> 00:00:44.870
if I have a selector that says div,
